Having extracted meaningful features from trajectory segments (see Sect. "Feature extraction" for feature extraction), the Mann-Whitney U-test, a non-parametric statistical test, was employed to select relevant features using SciPy24. To mitigate against group testing p-value inflation, a family-wise error rate (FWER) controlling procedure utilising Bonferroni correction was used. Features that demonstrated statistically significant differences between groups with rejection of the null hypothesis at an FWER < 0.05 were selected. Additionally, a Spearman correlation matrix was computed to identify collinearity between features. Pairs of features with high correlation (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:\rho\:>0.85$$\end{document}) were flagged, and one feature from each pair was removed to minimise redundancy, prevent multicollinearity, and enhance model stability and generalisability.

